#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:182
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The shown kernel configuration should allow the kernel image to boot both as a\n"
"host as well as a guest. However, if you want to, you can slim down the guest\n"
"image kernel considerably. Refer to the Xen documentation for more information.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:188
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Once the kernel is built you'll find the kernel image immediately in the\n"
"build directory (not inside <path>arch/</path> or any other directory) called\n"
"<path>vmlinuz</path>. Copy it to <path>/boot</path> and then configure your\n"
"bootloader to use the Xen hypervisor (one of the components installed\n"
"previously) which is stored as <path>/boot/xen.gz</path>. In the bootloader\n"
"configuration, add your newly built kernel as the kernel that Xen should\n"
"boot. For instance, for GRUB:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:197
#, no-wrap
msgid "GRUB Configuration for Xen"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:198
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"title Xen Gentoo Linux 3.5\n"
"root (hd0,0)\n"
"kernel /boot/xen.gz\n"
"module /boot/kernel-3.5.x.y-xen0 root=/dev/sda3\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:205
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Now reboot your system into Xen and check if you can do whatever you\n"
"normally do on your system. If this is the case, you can edit your\n"
"bootloader configuration to always boot into Xen.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><note>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:211
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you wish to start guest domains automatically on boot add <c>xendomains</c>\n"
"to the default runlevel as well and create a symlink in\n"
"<path>/etc/xen/auto/</path> to the Xen configuration files for the domains\n"
"you wish to start.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><title>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:221
#, no-wrap
msgid "Creating an Unpriviledged Domain"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:227
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Go to the Xen-powered Linux kernel source and, if necessary, update the\n"
"configuration. It is wise to keep as many topics as possible similar to\n"
"the main kernel. Then build the kernel\n"
"and place the resulting <path>vmlinuz</path> file where you want (we assume this\n"
"is <path>/mnt/data/xen/kernel</path>):\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:234
#, no-wrap
msgid "Building the guest kernel"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:235
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"~# <i>make O=~/build/domU</i>\n"
"~# <i>cp ~/build/domU/vmlinuz /mnt/data/xen/kernel/kernel-3.5.x.y-xen</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:242
#, no-wrap
msgid "Creating the Domain Disks"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:246
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"For best performance, it is best to dedicate a partition (or logical volume) to\n"
"a domain rather than a file based filesystem. However, if you are going to use\n"
"Xen primarily for tests using a file based filesystem does have its advantages\n"
"(especially regarding maintenance).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:253
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You can create a file based filesystem using <c>dd</c> and <c>mke2fs</c> (or\n"
"any other file system creation tool). For instance, to create a 4 Gbyte ext4\n"
"filesystem:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:258
#, no-wrap
msgid "Creating a file based filesystem"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:259
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"~# <i>dd if=/dev/zero of=/mnt/data/xen/disks/ext4root.img bs=1M count=4096</i>\n"
"~# <i>mkfs.ext4 /mnt/data/xen/disks/ext4root.img</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:266
#, no-wrap
msgid "Configuring a Domain"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:270
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Next we create a Xen configuration file for a domain. You can store these\n"
"configuration files where you want, for instance at\n"
"<path>/mnt/data/xen/configs</path>. As an example, we create a configuration\n"
"file for a small Gentoo environment which uses the disk image we created\n"
"previously:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:277
#, no-wrap
msgid "Creating a domain configuration file"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:278
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"~# <i>nano -w /mnt/data/xen/configs/gentoo</i>\n"
"\n"
"kernel = \"/mnt/data/xen/kernel/kernel-3.5.x.y-xen\"\n"
"memory = 512\n"
"name   = \"gentoo\"\n"
"<comment>(Map the disk image to the virtual /dev/sda1)</comment>\n"
"disk   = ['file:/mnt/data/xen/disks/ext4root.img,sda1,w']\n"
"root   = \"/dev/sda1 ro\"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:289
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you are using a block device (such as an lvm volume or partition) for\n"
"the disk use 'phy:' instead of 'file:' and leave off /dev. For example:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:293
#, no-wrap
msgid "Using a block device"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:294
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<comment>(LVM Volume)</comment>\n"
"disk = [ 'phy:lvm/xen-guest-root,sda1,w' ]\n"
"\n"
"<comment>(Physical Partition)</comment>\n"
"disk = [ 'phy:sdb6,sda1,w' ]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:302
#, no-wrap
msgid "You can find example configuration files in <path>/etc/xen</path>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:308
#, no-wrap
msgid "Launching the New Domain"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:312
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Now we're all set and we can launch the new domain. If the disk image contained\n"
"an operating system, we could just create and attach the domain using the\n"
"<c>xl</c> command:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:317
#, no-wrap
msgid "Creating and starting a new domain"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:318
#, no-wrap
msgid "~# <i>xl create /mnt/data/xen/configs/gentoo -c</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:322
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The domain would be booted inside the terminal in which you executed the\n"
"command. However, in our case, the disk image is empty so the domain won't boot\n"
"up in anything useful. To fix this, you can loop-mount the image and install\n"
"Gentoo as you're used to.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:329
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you want to disconnect from the domain, press <path>Ctrl+]</path>. You can\n"
"always reconnect to the domains' console using <c>xl console gentoo</c>.\n"
"However, there is only one console per domain, so only use it when you can't\n"
"access the domain otherwise (for instance, through SSH).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><title>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:339
#, no-wrap
msgid "Networking on Unpriviledged Domains"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:345
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Xen works best when using a bridged mode network configuration.\n"
"This means that your default network interface on\n"
"the administrative domain becomes a bridge which accepts connections to the\n"
"virtual domains as well as to the IP address your administrative domain has.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:354
#, no-wrap
msgid "Bridged Interfaces"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:358
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Create a bridge interface by creating a new link to the networking init script\n"
"as provided by Gentoo:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:362
#, no-wrap
msgid "Creating a bridge interface"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:363
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>cd /etc/init.d</i>\n"
"# <i>ln -s net.lo net.br0</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:368
#, no-wrap
msgid "Next, edit <path>/etc/conf.d/net</path> and setup the bridge:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:371
#, no-wrap
msgid "Enabling the bridge br0 interface"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:372
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>nano -w /etc/conf.d/net</i>\n"
"\n"
"bridge_br0=\"eth0\"\n"
"config_br0=\"192.168.1.200 netmask 255.255.255.0 brd 192.168.1.255\"\n"
"routes_br0=\"default via 192.168.1.1\"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:380
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Finally, install the <e>net-misc/bridge-utils</e> package, and make sure the\n"
"<path>net.br0</path> init script is loaded at boot.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:384
#, no-wrap
msgid "Finishing the bridge setup"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/xen-guide.xml:385
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>emerge net-misc/bridge-utils</i>\n"
"# <i>rc-update add net.br0 default</i>\n"
msgstr ""

